The paper focuses on the transfer of CNN features for image search and classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the benchmarking of different CNN layers and the combination of features, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of features for information retrieval (cs.IR) and the improvement of state-of-the-art benchmarks, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
